Great workout! I was in a Latin dance group in college, but have been somewhat out of shape in a while since I've found it difficult to workout when not doing it through dance, so this playlist is a great way to get back into it--so thank you!
But coming from a Latin dancer, there were some slight cultural/dance inaccuracies in this video (as there are in a lot of Zumba/Latin dance workouts), and there was a comment made about how the Caribbean dance is different from Latin dance, when they're actually not mutually exclusive since many Latin American countries are in or partially in the Caribbean! I only say this because as Zumba has become more commercial and accepted in the mainstream, the history and roots of Latin music (and dance) have gotten a little bit lost.

Dieta de los monjes de Brasil

Miércoles

1. Coloque por la mañana en media taza o vaso de agua, el número de granos de arroz correspondiente al número de kilos que quiere bajar.
2. No ponga más granos de los que necesita porque esos kilos nunca los recuperarás.
3. En la noche, tómese el agua dejando los granos para luego volver a llenar la taza hasta la mitad.

Jueves

Por la mañana en ayunas, beba de nuevo toda el agua dejando los granos de arroz y vuelva a llenar la taza hasta la mitad con agua.

Viernes

Por la mañana en ayunas, beba toda el agua junto con los granos de arroz.

Importante

1. Conserve la taza tapada durante todo el procedimiento.
2. Reparta copias de esta dieta conforme a los kilos que desea perder.
3. Comience la dieta el miércoles no antes de haber repartido todas las copias.
4. Puede repartir la dieta a cualquier persona.
5. No haga régimen aunque resulte increíble, FUNCIONA.

Nota:
Si la haces tal cual se indica, respetas todo y no pones 70 granos de arroz sino 5 o 7, un número lógico, desde ya en un mes según el organismo, bajas esos kilos sin siquiera darte cuenta. Pero ten en cuenta tener "FE

I'm sorry but I just have to tell a little story here.
I had hip hop dance lessons for 5 years but then I had to quit because I had to concentrate on school and the group I danced with gave me really bad vibes. They didn't bully me but they simply didn't talk to me. That was mainly because this group was meant for slightly older girls and I only got into it because I had the spirit. Additionally, the other girls all knew each other and I was alone for most of these 5 years.
Me quitting the group was 3 years ago and recently I got back into dancing to improve my mental and physical health. Because, not to be sappy or anything, both were going downhill due to things like stressful school stuff and a toxic boyfriend.
Anyways, I started rehearsing my old routines and was so full of joy. It was awesome, but I wanted to have a fitness aspect too.
Then I simply searched "zumba dance workout" and found this video. It was very hard for me but I pulled through and was so happy to not be alone in my room dancing. Well, I still was but this video didn't make me feel that.
To get to the point, thank you very much for this video and I hope you are well in these crazy times <3

I'm going to do this for a week from tomorrow morning and I'll come back and tell you my results. I'll also take my initial measurements tomorrow morning.
Day 1 - My measurements are as follows
Height - 157cm
Weight -76.2kg
Waist - 84cm
Arms - 34cm
Hips - 110cm
I just completed it and I'm sweating like crazy. I enjoyed it and the time went by so fast.
Day2 - Just completed day 2 and I'm on fire, enjoyed it. I added 10 minutes arms and 10 minutes abs workouts
Day3 - For some reason today was more difficult to finish but I stayed till the end. I am exhausted, adding in 20 minutes glutes this evening
Day 4 - Done, added in 20 minutes arms and abs
Day 5 - only managed to do 20 minutes, I had surgery in my left ankle over a year ago and it was quite painful today. Hopefully tomorrow will be better.
Day 6 - Completed and did another 10 minutes to make up for yesterday. It's getting easier to complete and I know most of the moves off by heart now
Day 7 - completed, I'm so happy. I'll be taking my final measurements tomorrow morning
My new measurements are as follows:
Weight: 75.9kg (lost 0.3 kg, my goal was 0.5, could it be that the muscles I was working had a role in this?) I'm happy either way
Waist: 81.6 (lost 2.4cm)
Arms: 33.5 (lost 0.5cm) this is a very big problem area and I'm so happy
Hips: 110cm (no change) I worked my glutes with weights because I'm not trying to lose the bit of ass I have lol
Overall I am happy with the results and they are quite realistic. I ate at a caloric deficit of 500 but I think I could've done better with the quality of food I was eating. I was also intermittent fasting and waist training.
I'll continue to do this workout (not every day though cos I get bored easily)

Alright.... so, for those trying to figure out their calories burned, I’m just dropping a formula here for you.
You need to know your METS. For fast dancing, the Mets equal 5

Formula:
(METs * 3.5 * your weight in kilograms)
Divide total by 200
Times total by the amount of minutes you are working out

Pounds to kilograms formula:
Your weight divided by 2.2

Here’s mine as an example:
I weigh 200 pounds, so I’m about 91 kilograms

(5*3.5*91)= 1,592.5
1,592.5 divided by 200=7.9625
7.9625 *(multiplied by) 60=477.75
I round down at this point.
So I’ve burned about 477 calories for this dance.

I'm going to do this workout every day for a week and share my results with you guys, please like and comment for motivation!!

Height: 165cm
Initial weight: 71kg

Day 1: Sweating a lot but it was really fun! Looking forward for the rest of the week

Day 2: still as challenging as the first day but loving it! Also, I do the whole 30 mins without stopping for the water break or any other time

Day 3: I've pretty much learned the movements by now so I can do the choreo more easily and keep up with the trainer better

Day 4: around the last 6 minutes it still feels exhausting but I feel so accomplished every time I finish it :)

Day 5: the workout felt shorter that usual today, I guess it's getting easier! 😁 I also feel a lot more energized throughout the day

Day 6: it feels really easy to keep up now, but it still gets my heart rate going! Excited for the last day tomorrow 😁

Day 7: I've done it!! I feel so happy that I could stick to this for a week, it's been really fun! I will weigh myself tomorrow morning and let you know if I've lost any weight 😊

Results: I weight 70.4kg! That means in a week I've lost 0.6kg, wich I think is a very healthy rate of losing weight. I haven't changed anything in my diet, I've just tried to eat smaller portions and eat very little for dinner.

I hope this was helpful for those who are thinking of doing this workout! I will definitely be continuing with other dance routines. Good luck everyone 😁

I really enjoyed this dance workout, but I really wish fitness trainers would be more mindful of the things they say during workouts and how their words may impact someone in that setting. I was really thrown when Nicole said, "Love yourself. If you don't, no one else will." A lot of people do these workouts as a means of self care and may be struggling with depression and a lack of self-confidence. What Nicole said isn't true, for one thing; many people who struggle to love themselves have (and NEED!) loving, supportive people in their lives. It's also a damaging thing to tell someone who's going through these struggles; people need to believe they are worthy of love even when they struggle to love themselves, and saying otherwise in such a casual, matter-of-fact way makes that harder to believe. I don't think Nicole intended to be hurtful (I really believe she just wants to encourage confidence and positivity, which is good!), but it's important to think about the way you choose to express something.

I noticed that specific comment, too. As you said, I am sure it wasn't meant in any hurtful manner; seemed like she said it to motivate, but I would say I have a healthy relationship with self esteem and confidence, good friends, family and yet, I noticed it. I hope that no one has taken this to heart and it has set them back, as this is a fantastic workout, with a true feel-good vibe, meant to inspire and be fun.
